records.addlTxt:
Defendant Rene Valdez in court with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.  Shawn N Woller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea as to counts 3 and 5. Counts 1, 2, 4 and 6 are dismissed and read-in. Court imposed the following sentence:

   The Defendant was sentenced to the following:  AS TO EACH COUNT CONSECUTIVE

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 1/2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT 
  -  1 1/2 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  

* Random  Drug Tests
*No Use or Possession controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;

RESTITUTION:  $594.00 (apply to count 1 only)  (to be paid as a condition of probation to the Waukesha County Metro Drug Unit);

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 on each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 6 months each count consecutive with each other, 1st 4 1/2 month with huber, STAYED the last 1 1/2 months,  to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours. Sentence to commence 02/22/2016 by 6 pm.   

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
